04/02/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Cyprus President Demetris Christofias voiced hope on Thursday (February 3rd) in Athens that a solution to the Cyprus issue would be found by the end of the year. Christofias briefed Greek Prime Minister George Papandreou about his recent meeting with UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon. He met with Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu in Geneva in late January to discuss progress in talks to reunify the divided island. Papandreou reaffirmed that the Cyprus issue remains a top priority of Greek foreign policy. The two officials called on Turkey and the Turkish Cypriots to take a constructive stance towards reunification talks. (Famagusta Gazette - 04/02/11; ANA-MPA, eKathimerini - 03/02/11)
